## Fix

### Enable Scan on Push and Enhanced Scanning

```bash
# Enable enhanced scanning (Amazon Inspector) for the account
aws inspector2 enable --resource-types ECR

# Enable scan on push per repository
aws ecr put-image-scanning-configuration \
    --repository-name webapp \
    --image-scanning-configuration scanOnPush=true
```

### Terraform Fix

See `terraform/ecr-fixed.tf` — includes `scan_on_push = true`, lifecycle policy, and KMS encryption.

### Jenkins Pipeline — Gate on ECR Scan Results

```groovy
stage('Wait for ECR Scan') {
    steps {
        script {
            // Wait for ECR scan to complete after push
            sh """
                aws ecr wait image-scan-complete \
                    --repository-name ${ECR_REPO} \
                    --image-id imageDigest=${IMAGE_DIGEST} \
                    --region ${AWS_REGION}
            """

            // Check scan results
            def critical = sh(
                script: """
                    aws ecr describe-image-scan-findings \
                        --repository-name ${ECR_REPO} \
                        --image-id imageDigest=${IMAGE_DIGEST} \
                        --query 'imageScanFindings.findingSeverityCounts.CRITICAL' \
                        --output text
                """,
                returnStdout: true
            ).trim()

            if (critical != 'None' && critical.toInteger() > 0) {
                error("SECURITY GATE: ${critical} CRITICAL CVEs found in ECR scan")
            }
            echo "ECR scan passed — no critical vulnerabilities"
        }
    }
}
```

